  "prompt": "Will I pass a drug test in 2 weeks as a non regular smoker?",
  "response": "The detection time for marijuana in urine tests can vary based on several factors, including frequency of use, metabolism, body fat, and the sensitivity of the test itself. As a non-regular smoker, you might have a better chance of passing a drug test compared to regular users. Here are some general guidelines:\n\n- **Occasional use (once or twice a week):** THC can typically be detected in urine for up to 1-3 weeks.\n- **Regular use (several times a week):** THC can be detected for up to 4-6 weeks.\n- **Heavy use (daily):** THC can be detected for more than 6 weeks.\n\nGiven that you are a non-regular smoker, there's a good chance you could pass a drug test in 2 weeks, but it's not guaranteed. Factors like your metabolism and the specific test being used can influence the outcome.\n\nIf you're concerned about passing the test, you might consider the following steps:\n\n1. **Stop using marijuana immediately** to give your body the maximum time to clear the THC.\n2. **Stay hydrated** and maintain a healthy diet and exercise routine, which can help your body metabolize and eliminate THC faster.\n3. **Consider detox products** if you're extremely concerned, though their effectiveness can vary and some may not be reliable.\n\nRemember, the only sure way to pass a drug test is to abstain from using marijuana and other substances that might be tested for. If you have specific concerns or a critical need to pass the test, consulting with a healthcare professional might provide more personalized advice.",
